# Faberon frontend

Read `CONSTITUTION.md` and `skills/build-faberon-frontend/SKILL.md` before modifying the frontend. For color/token work also follow `skills/minimize-color-palette`. For reviews follow `skills/review-faberon-frontend`.

- Enter `frontend` before running application, pnpm, Node, lint, test, or build commands.
- Treat pages and named modals as containers; keep child components presentational (typed props and callbacks only).
- Keep every Zustand store in `frontend/src/store` (domain folders allowed); never inside a page or modal folder.
- Put global dialogs in `frontend/src/modals`, register names in `store/modals/types.ts`, open via the modals store (LIFO), render from `ModalsHost` only.
- Define product colors, fonts, shadows, layout sizes, and exceptional visual values in `frontend/src/styles/index.css`.
- Use semantic Tailwind tokens and standard spacing/radius/font-size utilities; use MUI selectively without a competing theme.
- Preserve semantic HTML, labels, keyboard access, focus visibility, contrast, and responsive behavior.
- Use Node 26 and pnpm. Run `pnpm lint` and `pnpm build` from `frontend` before handoff.
